@startuml
title Arquitectura de Threads — Servidor

class Server {
  + run()
}

class Acceptor extends Thread {
  + run()
}

class GameLoop extends Thread {
  - game: Game
  - input_queue: Queue<PlayerCommand>
  + run()
}

class ClientHandler {
  - sender: Sender
  - receiver: Receiver
  - input_queue: Queue<PlayerCommand>&
  - output_queue: Queue<ServerEvent>
}

class Sender extends Thread {
  - output_queue: Queue<ServerEvent>
  - protocol: ServerProtocol
  + run()
}

class Receiver extends Thread {
  - input_queue: Queue<PlayerCommand>
  - protocol: ServerProtocol
  + run()
}

class ServerProtocol {
  + send_event(ev: ServerEvent)
  + recv_command(): ClientCommand
}

class Queue<T> {
  + push(item: T)
  + pop(): T
  + try_pop(item: T&): bool
  + try_push(item: T): bool
}

Server --> Acceptor: crea
Server --> GameLoop: crea
Acceptor --> ClientHandler: crea por conexión
ClientHandler *-- Sender
ClientHandler *-- Receiver
GameLoop --> Queue: pop() comandos
Receiver --> Queue: push() comandos
GameLoop --> ClientHandler: push() eventos
ClientHandler --> "out" Queue: eventos privados
Sender --> Queue: pop() eventos
Sender --> ServerProtocol
Receiver --> ServerProtocol
note right of Queue
  Cola MPMC bloqueante
  Thread-safe
end note
@enduml